XFS: stub __this_address on wasm32

Clang's wasm32 backend does not implement the GCC "address-of-label"
operator (&&label) — it emits

    fatal error: error in backend: WebAssembly hasn't implemented
    computed gotos

for any code path that evaluates &&label. XFS' __this_address macro
relies on &&__here to capture a diagnostic source location, which is
threaded into XFS error/warning printk calls as a void* and never
dereferenced. On wasm we replace it with ((void *)0); the kernel still
compiles, XFS messages just lose the per-callsite address (they keep
__func__ context).

Applied only to the wasm LKL build by scripts/oot_fs.sh stage --wasm.

--- a/fs/xfs/xfs_linux.h
+++ b/fs/xfs/xfs_linux.h
@@ -130,8 +130,14 @@
  * Return the address of a label.  Use barrier() so that the optimizer
  * won't reorder code to refactor the error jumpouts into a single
  * return, which throws off the reported address.
+ *
+ * wasm32 (clang) has no &&label operator -- fall back to a null address.
  */
+#if defined(__wasm__) || defined(__wasm32__)
+#define __this_address	((void *)0)
+#else
 #define __this_address	({ __label__ __here; __here: barrier(); &&__here; })
+#endif

 #define howmany(x, y)	(((x)+((y)-1))/(y))
